Copy this file to .env and fill in your OPNsense details.

This file is used by the Rust application to connect to your OPNsense API.

It should be kept secret and is ignored by .dockerignore and .gitignore.

--- OPNsense API Credentials ---

OPN_API_KEY="YOUR_OPNSENSE_API_KEY"
OPN_API_SECRET="YOUR_OPNSENSE_API_SECRET"

--- OPNsense & WireGuard URLs ---

Base URL for your OPNsense web UI (e.g., https://www.google.com/search?q=https://192.168.1.1 or https://www.google.com/search?q=https://opnsense.my-domain.com)

OPN_BASE_URL="https://www.google.com/search?q=https://your-opnsense-domain.com"

Public endpoint for your WireGuard server (e.g., https://www.google.com/search?q=wg.my-domain.com:51820)

WG_SERVER_ENDPOINT="https://www.google.com/search?q=your-wireguard-endpoint.com:51820"

--- WireGuard Server Details ---

The public key of the WireGuard server instance running on OPNsense

WG_SERVER_PUBLIC_KEY="YOUR_WG_SERVER_PUBLIC_KEY"

--- OPNsense UUIDs ---

Find these in your OPNsense UI/API

This is the UUID of the Server instance (under VPN -> WireGuard -> Server)

OPN_SERVER_UUID="YOUR_OPNSENSE_SERVER_INSTANCE_UUID"

This is the UUID of the Local instance (under VPN -> WireGuard -> Local)

OPN_WG_INSTANCE_UUID="YOUR_OPNSENSE_WG_LOCAL_INSTANCE_UUID"